  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Ellis Gray Loring opposes the plan for inviting George Thompson to come to the United States and work for the American Anti-Slavery Society as a lecturer. He doesn&apos;t think that Thompson should be invited here to preach Disunion and the overthrow of the government. He criticizes G. T.&apos;s oratory. &quot;In briefer terms, he did not (like Garrison and Phillips) hit the nail on the head...&quot; Loring also said: &quot;I feel happy and grateful for what you tell me about our beloved Lucia&apos;s health.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
